        NOTE: This is only called when a class CelestialBody requires a Coordinate, meaning it is guaranteed that the values will not be null when this is called

        the updated coordinate

      • toCoordinate

        public Coordinate toCoordinate()

        Method that will take the class Update.Request hours, minutes, seconds, and declination and return a new class Coordinate object.

        Realistically, this should never happen, but should be accounted for just in case it does. (i.e. Updating a Celestial Body from 'The Sun' to 'Crab Nebula' will result in this case)

        NOTE: This is only called in the event that the request has been validated and a class Coordinate is required for the particular class CelestialBody, guaranteeing that none of the fields are null

        See Also:
        class Update.Request, class Coordinate, class Coordinate, class CelestialBody
